<%# Flat alphabetical list (matching the styles dropdown): no wrapper span — the
    option content is bare text + a quiet "· Type" suffix, so it sits in the same
    .hw-combobox__option box as a style option and the rows match height. The
    suffix carries canton/city/venue, so a name is never ambiguous. %><% type = Location.type_for(combobox_value) %><%= combobox_display %><span class="loc-type"> &middot; <%= t("events.filter.location_types.#{type}") %></span>
